The Senator Teslim Folarin family has released the details of Barrister (Chief) Angela Nwaka Folarin’s burial programme. The wife of the Ibadan chief and federal lawmaker died in London on Friday, 28th January 2022 at the age of 47. Special Adviser on Media and Publicity to the Oyo Central lawmaker, Com. YSO Olaniyi released the details to journalists in Ibadan on Saturday. The full details read: “Please Join Us As We Say Goodbye To Our Loving Wife, Mother, Sister and Friend: Barrister (Chief) Angela Nwaka Folarin [Yeye Ayingun Olubadan]. “DATE: Tuesday, 22nd February 2022. TIME: 8:00am. VENUE: Sacred Heart Catholic Church, Beside Butoal Filling Station, Iyana Bodija On Iwo Road-Ojoo Expressway, Ibadan. “Laying to rest follows immediately after Church Service, at Eternal Home, Km25, Ibadan-Oyo Road Motunde, Afijio LGA. “Please be assured that adequate security measures are in place to ensure the safety of lives and properties during the burial rites”.